properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 13 at 9:27PM CST until January 14 at 3:00AM CST by NWS Hastings NE
properties.description:
* WHAT...Visibility around one quarter mile or less in dense fog.

* WHERE...In Kansas, Smith and Osborne Counties. In Nebraska,
Webster County.

* WHEN...Until 3 AM CST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility.
In addition, sub-freezing surface temperatures may combine
with fog to cause slick spots, especially on bridges and
overpasses.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Visibility will vary somewhat tonight, and
dense fog will probably not occur the entire time the Advisory
is in effect. As drier air moves in from the west overnight, any
dense fog will gradually dissipate from west-to-east.
properties.instruction:
If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of
distance ahead of you.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 AM CST TUESDAY
